00:20:40.080 --> 00:20:46.080
So they had an increase of visitor, they have an
increase of unique visitors. They can see that the

00:20:46.080 --> 00:20:51.120
transcriptions are being read and they can see 
they have more people visiting their podcast.

00:20:51.120 --> 00:20:57.680
And why transcript matter, there's a huge list.
Because podcasts right now without transcriptions

00:20:57.680 --> 00:21:03.680
they are inaccessible to deaf people, hard of 
hearing people, people with hearing insensitivity,

00:21:03.680 --> 00:21:10.320
people with ADHD, people in noisy environment,
people in silent environment as the train or the

00:21:10.320 --> 00:21:16.320
library. And transcripts are also good for the 
search engine, people's primary language isn't

00:21:16.320 --> 00:21:22.480
English, and also for fast referencing or quoting. 
So imagine you have a podcast and it was a hit

00:21:22.480 --> 00:21:26.960
and you have it on your WordPress website your 
WordPress website is super accessible. You have

00:21:26.960 --> 00:21:32.480
a podcast that just went viral, but now you have 
problem. You don't have transcript so Google won't

00:21:32.480 --> 00:21:39.040
be indexing it and you're going to use lose out on 
a huge group of people for which is inaccessible.

00:21:39.760 --> 00:21:45.120
And that fast reference quoting and imagine 
a journalist came to your website to write

00:21:45.120 --> 00:21:50.400
about your podcast and the person has it, really 
doesn't have time to go listen to all podcast.

00:21:50.960 --> 00:21:54.720
And in this sense, transcripts are very 
good, because people can scan them really

00:21:54.720 --> 00:22:00.240
fast looking for the point and they can quote 
from it and they can reference it in an article

00:22:00.240 --> 00:22:04.640
or another website. So the advantages 
of having transcripts are enormous.

00:22:05.360 --> 00:22:11.040
So how inclusion works and why I'm going to 
tell you this, because when you have a project

00:22:11.040 --> 00:22:16.640
and maybe even a small project, it's always good 
to have someone outside your bubble giving you

00:22:16.640 --> 00:22:22.640
feedback and their point of view on your product. 
It doesn't help you to have a bubble of the same

00:22:22.640 --> 00:22:29.360
people who think like you, are the same culture of 
you. So diversity is having a seat at the table.

00:22:30.000 --> 00:22:34.640
Inclusion is having a voice, and 
belonging is having that voice heard.

00:22:35.280 --> 00:22:40.720
I'm a person who can be considered the diversity 
in the Netherlands, because I am not Dutch.

00:22:41.280 --> 00:22:48.080
I'm chronic ill and I'm deaf and many times that 
happens that people ask me to join them and to be,

00:22:48.080 --> 00:22:53.440
you know, the other voice. And that's very nice to 
be sitting there and it's nice to be talking, but

00:22:53.440 --> 00:22:59.120
sometimes you talk and people don't listen. And 
so it's very important when you expand your bubble

00:22:59.680 --> 00:23:04.320
to really be aware, I am really listening 
to this person's voice. I'm not saying you

00:23:04.320 --> 00:23:10.000
have to do everything someone tells you, but one 
should really listen and you know comprehend what

00:23:10.000 --> 00:23:15.040
they are being told about their website about the 
product. And that's the best way to be inclusive.

00:23:16.320 --> 00:23:20.960
And now I'm going to give you a perspective, 
because uh since I've been doing this, I

00:23:20.960 --> 00:23:27.120
got that question many many times: but it costs 
money, it costs money, it costs money. And the

00:23:27.120 --> 00:23:31.360
first thing you have to think about when you 
have a budget and you're getting ready for stuff,

